text: Ingredients: - 1 (16.5 oz) refrigerated sugar cookie dough - 1 (15 oz) can pumpkin puree - 2 tablespoons granulated sugar - 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon - 1/4 teaspoon ground nutmeg - 1/4 teaspoon salt - 1 cup milk - 1/4 cup unsalted butter, melted - 1 teaspoon vanilla extract - Powdered sugar, for dusting Instructions: 1.
Line an 8x8 inch baking dish with parchment paper. 2.
In a medium bowl, mix together the pumpkin puree, granulated sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt until well combined.
On a lightly floured surface, roll out the chilled cookie dough into a rectangle about 1/4 inch thick. 4.
Spread the pumpkin mixture evenly over the rolled-out dough, leaving a small border on all sides. 5.
Drizzle the melted butter over the pumpkin mixture.
Then, sprinkle the milk over the top of the butter. 6.
Using your hands or a rolling pin, carefully roll up the dough from one of the shorter sides, forming a tight spiral shape.
Cut the roll into 8 equal slices using a sharp knife. 7.
Place each slice cut side down in the prepared baking dish.
Cover the rolls loosely with foil and bake for 25 minutes. 8.
Remove the foil and continue baking for another 5-7 minutes, or until golden brown and cooked through. 9.
Let the rolls cool slightly before removing them from the baking dish.
Serve warm, dusted with powdered sugar if desired.
